1
00:00:00,285 --> 00:00:01,998
(Previously)
I brought one of my juniors to say hi.

2
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:03,256
His name is Veha.

3
00:00:03,456 --> 00:00:05,401
We've met before.

4
00:00:06,134 --> 00:00:08,050
About that day, I'm sorry.

5
00:00:08,320 --> 00:00:10,404
Whatever I think is mine,

6
00:00:10,705 --> 00:00:12,303
I don't let anyone else take it easily.

7
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:14,284
I'll open your eyes
to your boyfriend's true colors.

8
00:00:14,302 --> 00:00:16,284
He's a lying piece of shit.

9
00:00:24,457 --> 00:00:27,300
There's a 90% chance
Lion is cheating on me.

10
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:35,130
I'LL PROVE THAT LAST 10% TO YOU

11
00:00:39,305 --> 00:00:39,977
Here.

12
00:00:41,893 --> 00:00:43,102
How's it going?

13
00:00:43,585 --> 00:00:44,903
I asked you to look into Lion.

14
00:00:45,420 --> 00:00:46,200
Hmm…

15
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:49,899
My investigation?

16
00:00:50,075 --> 00:00:50,699
Yeah.

17
00:00:58,820 --> 00:01:00,897
Did anyone hit on him at the gym?

18
00:01:05,475 --> 00:01:07,000
That's a full-on affair.

19
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:08,610
Well…

20
00:01:08,857 --> 00:01:10,696
What? Just say it.

21
00:01:11,302 --> 00:01:11,980
Well…

22
00:01:12,411 --> 00:01:13,703
Kanit sent you, didn't he?

23
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,700
"A Dog and A Plane"
(Episode 3)

24
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,290
SEVERAL HOURS EARLIER

25
00:02:37,402 --> 00:02:38,460
Hi.

26
00:02:39,219 --> 00:02:40,150
You've eaten already, right?
Damn.

27
00:02:41,139 --> 00:02:43,000
He's so handsome.

28
00:02:44,525 --> 00:02:45,804
Handsome how?

29
00:02:46,296 --> 00:02:47,801
He's only saved by the uniform.

30
00:02:48,205 --> 00:02:51,000
You can find a face like his
at any market.

31
00:02:51,420 --> 00:02:52,998
I don't know what market
you're talking about,

32
00:02:53,088 --> 00:02:56,161
but it's definitely not our market.

33
00:02:57,448 --> 00:02:59,899
No wonder so many people want to date him.

34
00:03:00,438 --> 00:03:01,263
At this rate,

35
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:05,001
who's going to be left for us?

36
00:03:05,477 --> 00:03:07,401
It doesn't matter
how handsome or cool he is.

37
00:03:07,601 --> 00:03:08,998
If he's cheating on his boyfriend,

38
00:03:09,367 --> 00:03:11,099
he's an asshole.

39
00:03:11,819 --> 00:03:12,700
Hey!

40
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:15,296
Don't charge in just yet. Calm down.

41
00:03:15,770 --> 00:03:17,986
I know you feel strongly about this,
but stick to the plan.

42
00:03:18,340 --> 00:03:19,402
I'm calm.

43
00:03:21,115 --> 00:03:23,979
But if I catch him cheating on
his boyfriend right in front of me,

44
00:03:24,687 --> 00:03:26,702
his bones are going to crack
just like my knuckles.

45
00:03:27,700 --> 00:03:29,497
You're even more invested
than his boyfriend.

46
00:03:31,570 --> 00:03:32,257
Let's go.

47
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:53,982
After he gets off work,
he goes to the gym.

48
00:03:54,068 --> 00:03:55,102
He lives a routine life.

49
00:03:55,370 --> 00:03:56,798
It'll be easy for me to follow him.

50
00:03:57,176 --> 00:03:59,601
But do you really think
they'd hook up here?

51
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:01,700
Wouldn't it be better to go
to a love hotel?

52
00:04:01,765 --> 00:04:04,404
Oh, Ja-O. You know nothing.

53
00:04:04,757 --> 00:04:06,499
The gym is the ultimate place for that.

54
00:04:06,721 --> 00:04:09,499
It's where you can work out
and be seductive.

55
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:13,397
Muscles and the smell of sweat
tempt people to sin.

56
00:04:14,047 --> 00:04:16,835
People don't choose where they cheat.

57
00:04:17,297 --> 00:04:19,004
They'd even get together in hell.

58
00:04:19,041 --> 00:04:19,979
Whoa.

59
00:04:26,071 --> 00:04:26,998
Hey.

60
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,496
Someone's coming.

61
00:04:43,420 --> 00:04:44,200
Hey, bro.
Huh?

62
00:04:45,149 --> 00:04:47,097
Isn't that the flight attendant we met
during our escort job?

63
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:53,979
I just finished.

64
00:04:54,472 --> 00:04:55,500
Do you want to use it now?

65
00:04:56,152 --> 00:04:56,899
Alright.

66
00:04:57,277 --> 00:04:58,401
Damn.

67
00:04:59,354 --> 00:05:01,450
Is this a flight attendant showdown?

68
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:03,782
Wow. You're good at this.

69
00:05:03,819 --> 00:05:04,560
Wait.

70
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:07,499
Or are they just working out together?

71
00:05:08,822 --> 00:05:10,078
Let me help.

72
00:05:11,580 --> 00:05:13,056
I can tell from their body language.

73
00:05:13,251 --> 00:05:14,605
That's a full-on affair.

74
00:05:17,890 --> 00:05:18,750
Last one.

75
00:05:23,594 --> 00:05:25,974
Whose boyfriend are you? You're so fit.

76
00:05:27,314 --> 00:05:28,303
Yours.

77
00:05:29,390 --> 00:05:31,300
But when will I get to be
your real boyfriend?

78
00:05:31,521 --> 00:05:32,697
Hey.

79
00:05:32,925 --> 00:05:34,198
It won't be long now.

80
00:05:34,632 --> 00:05:35,985
We're going official soon.

81
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,970
Wow. Let me document this shit.

82
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:42,530
I forgot my phone.

83
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:43,980
Capture them, Ki.

84
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:44,997
Come on.

85
00:05:48,030 --> 00:05:48,891
Did you get it?

86
00:05:51,431 --> 00:05:52,402
Oh, shit.

87
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:53,610
- What?
- I forgot to charge my phone.

88
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:54,441
What?

89
00:05:55,296 --> 00:05:56,597
Ja-O, do it!

90
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,620
I have my phone.

91
00:05:59,078 --> 00:06:00,171
But I can't capture them.

92
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:01,200
Why not?

93
00:06:01,379 --> 00:06:02,398
The lens is cracked.

94
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,388
Then why even mention it?

95
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,800
I can't with my team.

96
00:06:14,770 --> 00:06:15,500
Excuse me.

97
00:06:19,056 --> 00:06:20,305
How can I help you?

98
00:06:21,136 --> 00:06:22,968
Uh… do you have a power bank
I could borrow?

99
00:06:22,995 --> 00:06:25,300
My friend's phone is dead.

100
00:06:25,588 --> 00:06:26,797
A power bank?

101
00:06:27,530 --> 00:06:30,300
Yes, I have one, but it's in my bag.

102
00:06:32,225 --> 00:06:34,832
Then, if it's not too much trouble,
can I borrow it?

103
00:06:36,395 --> 00:06:38,170
But it's in the locker.

104
00:06:38,765 --> 00:06:41,518
Wanna go inside and get it with me?

105
00:06:41,730 --> 00:06:43,570
Huh? What did you say?

106
00:06:43,782 --> 00:06:44,697
Wanna go?

107
00:06:44,903 --> 00:06:45,899
Go where?

108
00:06:46,327 --> 00:06:47,900
To get the power bank.

109
00:06:48,974 --> 00:06:50,197
Wanna go?

110
00:06:52,401 --> 00:06:53,896
Okay.

111
00:06:55,011 --> 00:06:56,404
I'll get you some water.

112
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:57,496
Okay.

113
00:06:58,300 --> 00:06:59,001
Hey.

114
00:06:59,762 --> 00:07:00,497
Go.

115
00:07:00,909 --> 00:07:01,602
Hurry!

116
00:07:03,940 --> 00:07:04,703
Wanna go?

117
00:07:05,777 --> 00:07:06,700
Oh, um…

118
00:07:07,551 --> 00:07:08,450
No, I'm good.

119
00:07:08,604 --> 00:07:09,700
No, you're not.

120
00:07:10,573 --> 00:07:11,979
There's still some battery left.

121
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:15,401
Do you still want the power bank or not?

122
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:18,102
Or do you actually want my number?

123
00:07:18,610 --> 00:07:19,594
Um, no.

124
00:07:20,915 --> 00:07:21,590
Oh.

125
00:07:23,730 --> 00:07:25,130
Got a problem with my boyfriend?

126
00:07:25,770 --> 00:07:26,897
You two are together?

127
00:07:27,285 --> 00:07:28,204
Of course.

128
00:07:28,333 --> 00:07:29,974
This is my boyfriend Toto.

129
00:07:30,481 --> 00:07:31,610
You don't believe me?

130
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:36,400
Darling.

131
00:07:37,881 --> 00:07:38,600
So?

132
00:07:38,647 --> 00:07:41,370
Were you talking with my boyfriend
because you wanted to hook up with him?

133
00:07:41,977 --> 00:07:42,900
Okay, okay.

134
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,882
- I know you're possessive of him.
- Yeah.

135
00:07:44,910 --> 00:07:46,402
- I'm going to leave him alone.
- Great.

136
00:07:46,909 --> 00:07:48,402
Why does this always happen to me?

137
00:07:48,568 --> 00:07:49,545
See you around.

138
00:07:50,470 --> 00:07:51,460
But don't do this again.

139
00:07:51,481 --> 00:07:54,650
I've dealt with a lot of homewreckers.

140
00:07:55,349 --> 00:07:56,100
How did I do?

141
00:07:57,140 --> 00:07:59,977
Am I qualified to join your
cheater-catching gang now?

142
00:08:00,042 --> 00:08:00,724
Yeah.

143
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,601
You're quick-witted. I'll give you that.

144
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:04,703
You freaking made me look like the uke.

145
00:08:05,029 --> 00:08:06,121
I have to go now.

146
00:08:06,151 --> 00:08:06,807
Okay.

147
00:08:07,198 --> 00:08:07,979
Good luck.

148
00:08:08,731 --> 00:08:09,601
I got in.

149
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:10,745
I can catch cheaters now.

150
00:08:10,840 --> 00:08:12,303
You won't be disappointed!

151
00:08:18,238 --> 00:08:19,696
Do you want me
to entertain you again today?

152
00:08:21,420 --> 00:08:22,297
Mr. Akki!

153
00:08:24,502 --> 00:08:25,800
You work out here too?

154
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:28,402
Yes, it's my first time here.

155
00:08:28,979 --> 00:08:30,597
I love that they have
so many machines here.

156
00:08:30,628 --> 00:08:32,200
You don't have to worry about
people stealing them.

157
00:08:32,653 --> 00:08:33,502
That's right.

158
00:08:33,810 --> 00:08:35,497
But it depends on the time, though.

159
00:08:35,678 --> 00:08:36,899
Sometimes it gets busy.

160
00:08:37,500 --> 00:08:39,697
But some people just steal
whenever they want.

161
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:41,601
They don't care if someone else
is already using them.

162
00:08:41,974 --> 00:08:43,404
They have no morals.

163
00:08:43,754 --> 00:08:45,198
I really hate people like that.

164
00:08:46,654 --> 00:08:48,530
I didn't know working out
had anything to do with morals.

165
00:08:48,677 --> 00:08:50,800
Morality holds the world together, so yes.

166
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,032
Some people have no shame.

167
00:08:53,917 --> 00:08:56,395
They mess with people
who are already taken.

168
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:59,302
Just because you're good-looking
doesn't mean you can do whatever you want.

169
00:09:01,690 --> 00:09:03,401
Are you still talking about working out?

170
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,482
Yes.

171
00:09:04,512 --> 00:09:06,299
Apply that to your real life.

172
00:09:27,890 --> 00:09:29,300
Kanit sent you, didn't he?

173
00:09:32,705 --> 00:09:35,099
He suspects
I'm two-timing him, doesn't he?

174
00:09:37,346 --> 00:09:38,004
What?

175
00:09:38,250 --> 00:09:39,395
Don't “what” me.

176
00:09:39,524 --> 00:09:40,700
I remember you.

177
00:09:40,958 --> 00:09:42,530
You're the lottery seller.

178
00:09:44,364 --> 00:09:48,197
No wonder I've been feeling like I'm
being followed and watched all the time.

179
00:09:48,918 --> 00:09:49,602
Yeah.

180
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:51,598
So what if Kanit sent me?

181
00:09:51,803 --> 00:09:52,895
It's nothing.

182
00:09:53,210 --> 00:09:56,896
But do you realize
you're making him overthink?

183
00:09:57,619 --> 00:09:59,802
He's already an overthinker,

184
00:10:00,142 --> 00:10:02,500
and now you're feeding him
exaggerated information.

185
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:04,902
You're making him feel even worse.
Do you understand?

186
00:10:05,390 --> 00:10:06,699
Exaggerated?

187
00:10:06,851 --> 00:10:08,400
I saw it with my own eyes.

188
00:10:08,463 --> 00:10:09,210
What's exaggerated?

189
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:11,700
That's just your interpretation
of what you saw.

190
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,100
Interpretation?

191
00:10:13,269 --> 00:10:14,358
You two were almost sucking lips.

192
00:10:14,383 --> 00:10:15,805
What else am I supposed to interpret?

193
00:10:15,899 --> 00:10:17,770
Were you doing an oral health checkup?

194
00:10:18,669 --> 00:10:19,977
What kind of toothpaste do you use?

195
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:20,810
The salt one?

196
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:23,730
What a lame excuse.

197
00:10:25,056 --> 00:10:29,397
Fine, I'll admit I'm not good
at managing relationships.

198
00:10:29,863 --> 00:10:32,204
But I'm fixing this.

199
00:10:34,442 --> 00:10:35,801
You don't understand

200
00:10:37,342 --> 00:10:39,200
what my relationship with Kanit is like.

201
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:40,400
You're an outsider.

202
00:10:43,703 --> 00:10:44,980
Let's not waste time.

203
00:10:45,014 --> 00:10:45,797
Here.

204
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:49,100
I'm giving you 50,000. Is this enough?

205
00:10:49,712 --> 00:10:50,997
From now on,

206
00:10:51,485 --> 00:10:52,328
stay out of this.

207
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:54,102
I'm going to fix the problem myself.

208
00:10:54,937 --> 00:10:57,300
You think every problem
can be solved with money?

209
00:10:57,761 --> 00:10:59,397
Then what do you want me to do?

210
00:11:00,869 --> 00:11:02,400
Please give me a chance.

211
00:11:03,490 --> 00:11:04,903
I really love Kanit.

212
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,400
One week.

213
00:11:12,234 --> 00:11:13,702
I'm giving you one week.

214
00:11:14,490 --> 00:11:17,398
Go talk to that flight attendant
and break it off for good.

215
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,397
Then tell Kanit yourself.

216
00:11:23,229 --> 00:11:24,300
Thank you so much.

217
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:28,497
I promise I'll sort everything out
within a week.

218
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:31,795
If you don't end it within a week,

219
00:11:32,647 --> 00:11:34,401
I'll tell Kanit myself.

220
00:11:36,903 --> 00:11:37,970
And about your money…

221
00:11:38,645 --> 00:11:39,450
Just keep it.

222
00:11:40,751 --> 00:11:42,503
Go buy some honesty with it.

223
00:11:43,210 --> 00:11:44,720
Maybe you'll find some for sale.

224
00:11:51,505 --> 00:11:53,601
Did anyone hit on him at the gym?

225
00:11:55,791 --> 00:11:56,696
No.

226
00:11:57,801 --> 00:11:59,001
I mean, wow,

227
00:11:59,349 --> 00:12:02,499
Lion lifts 40 kg on each side.
How does he even do that?

228
00:12:02,771 --> 00:12:03,802
He's so good.

229
00:12:04,197 --> 00:12:05,297
I can't even do that.

230
00:12:05,450 --> 00:12:06,800
- He's strong.
- So damn strong.

231
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:11,450
Hmm, then I don't think
he's cheating on me.

232
00:12:13,968 --> 00:12:15,050
You can stop spying on him.

233
00:12:16,397 --> 00:12:17,870
I can keep doing it a little longer.

234
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:20,598
Let me spy on him a bit more.

235
00:12:22,305 --> 00:12:23,297
But,

236
00:12:23,648 --> 00:12:25,398
I have a new job for you.

237
00:12:28,856 --> 00:12:29,598
Here.

238
00:12:29,992 --> 00:12:32,302
I'm going to take a cabin crew assessment.

239
00:12:33,099 --> 00:12:36,650
I need you to tutor me
for the practical test.

240
00:12:38,272 --> 00:12:38,998
Me?
Of course.

241
00:12:40,149 --> 00:12:40,878
Tutor you?

242
00:12:41,522 --> 00:12:42,266
I'm a rescuer.

243
00:12:42,290 --> 00:12:43,397
You're a flight attendant.

244
00:12:43,683 --> 00:12:44,706
What can I possibly teach you?

245
00:12:44,742 --> 00:12:45,870
How to push a cart?

246
00:12:45,900 --> 00:12:48,253
Look, flight attendants
have to help people too.

247
00:12:48,277 --> 00:12:50,798
You're a rescuer with experience.

248
00:12:50,819 --> 00:12:54,398
If you tutor me, I think
I'll do better than others.

249
00:12:57,016 --> 00:12:57,982
It's not that complicated.

250
00:12:58,066 --> 00:13:01,992
You just have to be prepared at all times
because emergencies are unpredictable.

251
00:13:02,026 --> 00:13:04,903
You have to be ready
to deal with them promptly.

252
00:13:05,070 --> 00:13:06,699
You have to stay alert at all times.

253
00:13:07,937 --> 00:13:08,604
That's it?
Yeah.

254
00:13:15,540 --> 00:13:16,330
Whoa.

255
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:17,801
I can feel it in my nose.

256
00:13:19,020 --> 00:13:20,057
It's spicy.

257
00:13:20,897 --> 00:13:21,899
So damn spicy.

258
00:13:22,899 --> 00:13:23,512
Hey!

259
00:13:23,539 --> 00:13:25,265
What do you do when it's spicy,
but you don't have anything to drink?

260
00:13:25,294 --> 00:13:26,539
This is an emergency. What do you do?

261
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:28,188
- It's burning. Give me that.
- Come on!

262
00:13:28,229 --> 00:13:30,087
This is an emergency. What do you do?

263
00:13:30,117 --> 00:13:31,385
- There's nothing to drink.
- Ugh, there's a drink!

264
00:13:31,420 --> 00:13:32,385
Stop turning this into a scenario.

265
00:13:32,413 --> 00:13:34,000
You asked me to tutor you.
This is an emergency situation.

266
00:13:34,023 --> 00:13:35,429
- There's nothing to drink.
- I'm dying here. Give me that drink!

267
00:13:35,451 --> 00:13:37,317
Open your mouth
and stick your tongue out like this.

268
00:13:37,343 --> 00:13:38,120
Give me the drink.

269
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:39,980
Stick your tongue out
and let the saliva drip out.

270
00:13:40,008 --> 00:13:40,733
Give it to me.

271
00:13:40,751 --> 00:13:41,859
It's not an emergency. Give me that.

272
00:13:41,881 --> 00:13:43,017
You said you wanted practice. Come on.

273
00:13:43,045 --> 00:13:44,527
This isn't an emergency. Give me that!

274
00:13:44,552 --> 00:13:46,103
You said you were dying just now.

275
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:47,588
Do you still want me to teach you or not?

276
00:13:47,617 --> 00:13:48,502
Come on.

277
00:13:51,728 --> 00:13:52,600
Open your mouth first.

278
00:13:52,870 --> 00:13:53,837
Open it wide.

279
00:13:54,453 --> 00:13:55,780
Yeah, now stick your tongue out.

280
00:13:55,813 --> 00:13:57,160
Hey, is that all the
tongue you have?

281
00:13:57,180 --> 00:13:58,742
Stick it out all the way.

282
00:13:59,070 --> 00:13:59,900
Look down.

283
00:14:00,370 --> 00:14:02,601
Yeah, then let your saliva flow.

284
00:14:04,087 --> 00:14:05,245
Enough. Give me the drink!

285
00:14:05,268 --> 00:14:07,506
One more time!
Let me see it properly and clearly.

286
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:09,314
Okay.

287
00:14:09,614 --> 00:14:12,320
Well done, good boy.
Which one's your drink?

288
00:14:12,342 --> 00:14:13,983
Here you go, good boy. Drink this.

289
00:14:15,074 --> 00:14:16,284
It's so spicy I'm dying.

290
00:14:16,620 --> 00:14:17,800
You made me act like a dog.

291
00:14:18,312 --> 00:14:20,607
Now that you mentioned it,
you actually look like one.

292
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:30,896
You want me to teach you.

293
00:14:31,103 --> 00:14:32,997
Are you physically and mentally prepared?

294
00:14:33,510 --> 00:14:34,804
What do I even need to prepare?

295
00:14:35,477 --> 00:14:37,290
Do you think being a rescuer is easy?

296
00:14:38,108 --> 00:14:40,540
I had to go through
physical and mental training

297
00:14:40,570 --> 00:14:41,850
to become the rescuer I am today.

298
00:14:42,226 --> 00:14:44,318
Being a rescuer is like being a superhero.

299
00:14:44,762 --> 00:14:47,171
You have to get there as fast as possible
to save humankind.

300
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,398
Come on.

301
00:14:50,518 --> 00:14:51,733
If you're going to teach me,
just teach me.

302
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:53,096
No need to brag.

303
00:14:55,980 --> 00:14:57,594
You have no idea how lucky you are

304
00:14:57,620 --> 00:14:59,604
to have the number
one rescuer teaching you.

305
00:15:00,521 --> 00:15:01,977
I'm giving up my time for this, you know.

306
00:15:03,025 --> 00:15:05,402
Look, you owe me money.

307
00:15:05,435 --> 00:15:06,699
You're not teaching me for free.

308
00:15:09,130 --> 00:15:09,897
Fine.

309
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:13,099
The first lesson I'm going to teach you

310
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:14,597
is…

311
00:15:16,127 --> 00:15:18,096
how to save someone's life

312
00:15:18,710 --> 00:15:20,100
with mouth-to-mouth.

313
00:15:21,736 --> 00:15:22,465
Ew!

314
00:15:23,328 --> 00:15:24,405
What are you doing?

315
00:15:26,490 --> 00:15:28,096
Did you dip your hand in a salt farm?

316
00:15:28,281 --> 00:15:29,179
It's so salty.
Stop being dramatic.

317
00:15:30,010 --> 00:15:32,900
Don't take advantage of the
situation to touch my soft lips.

318
00:15:33,260 --> 00:15:34,503
Your hand is that salty.

319
00:15:34,530 --> 00:15:35,980
I don't even want to imagine your lips.

320
00:15:37,745 --> 00:15:38,718
Hey! Hey! Hey!

321
00:15:39,570 --> 00:15:40,811
Fire!

322
00:15:41,235 --> 00:15:41,878
Hey!

323
00:15:42,260 --> 00:15:42,954
Fire!

324
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:44,465
He's on fire!

325
00:15:44,650 --> 00:15:46,576
- What do you do? He's on fire!
- Fire!

326
00:15:48,270 --> 00:15:50,201
- Come on!
- Fire!

327
00:15:59,725 --> 00:16:01,002
Hellfire engine oil.

328
00:16:01,026 --> 00:16:02,195
Pour it in. Rev it for fun.

329
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:05,866
Rev so hard
even the Hell Wardens come calling.

330
00:16:05,900 --> 00:16:07,720
♪ When I find love,
I wanna go out and play ♪

331
00:16:07,754 --> 00:16:09,967
♪ Invite you to dance away,
but we seem to go astray ♪

332
00:16:09,988 --> 00:16:11,979
What's going on?
Are you filming a commercial?

333
00:16:12,743 --> 00:16:13,500
No.

334
00:16:13,524 --> 00:16:14,862
That was your first lesson.

335
00:16:15,571 --> 00:16:16,300
What?

336
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:19,934
I specifically set up
a mock emergency scenario for you.

337
00:16:20,740 --> 00:16:22,899
Ugh! Did you really have to go this far?

338
00:16:23,157 --> 00:16:25,102
Fires can happen often.

339
00:16:25,310 --> 00:16:28,250
The most important thing is that
you have to stay calm.

340
00:16:29,150 --> 00:16:31,330
I was calm,
but I was having a heart attack.

341
00:16:31,460 --> 00:16:33,497
Good. That means you'll remember it.

342
00:16:33,583 --> 00:16:35,598
Once you remember,
you'll be able to respond in time.

343
00:16:35,663 --> 00:16:37,401
These things happen without warning.

344
00:16:37,518 --> 00:16:38,299
Seriously.

345
00:16:38,602 --> 00:16:39,496
And what's this?

346
00:16:39,668 --> 00:16:41,802
You look like you're filming
a commercial with celebrities.

347
00:16:42,337 --> 00:16:43,740
He hired me.

348
00:16:52,574 --> 00:16:53,398
Hey.

349
00:16:53,777 --> 00:16:55,167
Why did you bring me to your house?

350
00:16:55,758 --> 00:16:57,800
To get the equipment
I need to teach you with.

351
00:17:00,085 --> 00:17:01,897
Your house is nice and peaceful.

352
00:17:02,390 --> 00:17:03,982
It feels like a house in the countryside,

353
00:17:04,496 --> 00:17:06,094
but it's not that far
from the city center.

354
00:17:06,750 --> 00:17:08,503
It's the only thing my father left me.

355
00:17:08,936 --> 00:17:10,302
I have to take the best care of it.

356
00:17:16,256 --> 00:17:18,202
Hey. What's that smell?

357
00:17:19,721 --> 00:17:20,850
What's burning?

358
00:17:21,149 --> 00:17:21,897
Hey!

359
00:17:25,288 --> 00:17:25,974
Hey!

360
00:17:26,370 --> 00:17:26,888
Hey, bro.

361
00:17:26,906 --> 00:17:28,050
You ran over here looking
freaked out. What's wrong?

362
00:17:28,074 --> 00:17:29,410
I thought there was a fire.

363
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:30,300
Whoa.

364
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:31,294
What fire?

365
00:17:31,324 --> 00:17:32,899
I'm just having a pork BBQ with my friend.

366
00:17:32,955 --> 00:17:34,093
Hi, To.

367
00:17:34,757 --> 00:17:35,602
Hi.

368
00:17:35,856 --> 00:17:37,500
This is my friend Kanit.

369
00:17:38,122 --> 00:17:38,900
Hi.
Hi.

370
00:17:39,680 --> 00:17:41,201
Wanna have some meatballs with us?

371
00:17:41,282 --> 00:17:43,294
Oh, it's okay.
I've been cutting out carbs lately.

372
00:17:43,327 --> 00:17:44,791
There are no carbs.

373
00:17:44,819 --> 00:17:46,903
The meatballs are all pork.

374
00:17:47,139 --> 00:17:49,000
It's true. I can't stop eating them.

375
00:17:49,835 --> 00:17:50,600
Are they good?

376
00:17:50,680 --> 00:17:51,974
The best. Try them.

377
00:17:52,370 --> 00:17:53,697
Can I borrow this?

378
00:17:54,616 --> 00:17:55,982
Come on. Wanna have some?

379
00:17:56,262 --> 00:17:57,194
You go ahead.
Hey, try it.

380
00:17:58,468 --> 00:18:00,503
This is all fancy stuff.
Let me get some for you.

381
00:18:06,562 --> 00:18:07,247
Hey!
Lew!

382
00:18:08,114 --> 00:18:09,000
What's wrong?

383
00:18:09,220 --> 00:18:09,853
Lew!

384
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:12,097
- What's wrong?
- Did the meatball get stuck in your throat?

385
00:18:12,722 --> 00:18:13,263
Hey!

386
00:18:13,390 --> 00:18:14,934
Hey, what should we do?

387
00:18:15,388 --> 00:18:16,539
Hey! Save my sister's friend!

388
00:18:16,690 --> 00:18:17,325
Hey!

389
00:18:17,800 --> 00:18:18,882
Save my sister's friend!

390
00:18:18,906 --> 00:18:19,669
Hey! What should we do?

391
00:18:19,691 --> 00:18:20,801
Lew, are you okay?

392
00:18:21,271 --> 00:18:22,120
Get it out.

393
00:18:24,463 --> 00:18:25,445
Keng Bouncy Meatballs.

394
00:18:25,471 --> 00:18:26,617
So bouncy they jump
straight down your throat.

395
00:18:26,648 --> 00:18:29,983
Taste guaranteed by Mr. Pork Tenderloin!

396
00:18:30,002 --> 00:18:31,367
♪ When I find love,
I wanna go out and play ♪

397
00:18:31,394 --> 00:18:34,551
♪ Invite you to dance away,
but we seem to go astray ♪

398
00:18:34,699 --> 00:18:36,970
♪ Stumbling,
like rolling a boulder uphill all day ♪

399
00:18:36,995 --> 00:18:40,093
♪ Oh well, you know what they say,
single is where I stay ♪

400
00:18:40,108 --> 00:18:40,678
Hey.

401
00:18:41,524 --> 00:18:42,749
Are you acting like a celebrity again?

402
00:18:42,780 --> 00:18:43,955
Filming a commercial again?

403
00:18:43,989 --> 00:18:47,001
I wanted you to deal with
an unexpected situation.

404
00:18:47,331 --> 00:18:48,888
You did better than I thought.

405
00:18:48,914 --> 00:18:50,201
Amazing response.

406
00:18:50,570 --> 00:18:53,235
You could've just taught me properly,
not acted it out like this.

407
00:18:53,266 --> 00:18:54,700
Both you and your sister are unbelievable.

408
00:18:54,794 --> 00:18:56,099
I'm sorry, Kanit.

409
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:57,401
My brother forced me to do it.

410
00:18:57,509 --> 00:18:59,000
- Hey.
- I didn't want to be an actress.

411
00:18:59,050 --> 00:19:01,983
You said you didn't want to be an actress,
but your acting was so convincing.

412
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:11,201
I brought you to eat at this market

413
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:13,090
because there was
nothing left in my fridge.

414
00:19:13,121 --> 00:19:14,902
We used everything
to make that commercial for you.

415
00:19:15,416 --> 00:19:17,979
Hey, I don't need training anymore.

416
00:19:18,041 --> 00:19:21,700
I've already had so many intense things
happen today that I'm dizzy.

417
00:19:24,100 --> 00:19:24,903
Here.

418
00:19:26,736 --> 00:19:27,558
What is it?

419
00:19:27,691 --> 00:19:28,900
Try it. Come on.

420
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:32,170
PIPO GUMMY LEMON JEED

421
00:19:36,546 --> 00:19:37,435
Hmm…
How is it?

422
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:39,000
So zesty.

423
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:40,500
I feel better now. Can I have it?

424
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,977
Take it. I bought it for you.

425
00:19:45,370 --> 00:19:47,297
Wait a sec. I'm going to pee.

426
00:19:50,721 --> 00:19:52,300
Gummy Lemon Jeed.

427
00:19:53,487 --> 00:19:54,297
Really zesty.

428
00:19:58,108 --> 00:19:59,419
Help! Help!

429
00:19:59,447 --> 00:20:00,903
Someone's having a seizure!

430
00:20:01,050 --> 00:20:01,977
Help!

431
00:20:02,506 --> 00:20:03,900
Someone, please help!

432
00:20:03,933 --> 00:20:05,103
Someone's having a seizure!

433
00:20:05,238 --> 00:20:05,911
Uncle!

434
00:20:06,340 --> 00:20:07,706
Are you okay, Uncle?

435
00:20:09,130 --> 00:20:10,502
Call an ambulance.

436
00:20:10,982 --> 00:20:11,826
Can you call?

437
00:20:11,850 --> 00:20:12,903
Come on!

438
00:20:13,077 --> 00:20:13,982
Not again.

439
00:20:14,570 --> 00:20:16,628
I told you I don't need training anymore.

440
00:20:16,650 --> 00:20:18,811
I'm exhausted and dizzy
after everything that happened today.

441
00:20:18,832 --> 00:20:20,240
Come on.

442
00:20:20,887 --> 00:20:21,979
What's this, Uncle?

443
00:20:22,321 --> 00:20:23,237
So dramatic.

444
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:24,349
You're even having a seizure.

445
00:20:24,376 --> 00:20:26,592
Drooling and hands curled up. Whoa.

446
00:20:26,611 --> 00:20:28,625
How much did he pay you to do this?

447
00:20:28,662 --> 00:20:29,848
Someone, please help!

448
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:31,157
Oh, don't help him.

449
00:20:31,192 --> 00:20:32,091
He's just pretending.

450
00:20:32,118 --> 00:20:33,367
He's going to stand up soon.

451
00:20:33,397 --> 00:20:35,988
And once he does,
he's going to sell something.

452
00:20:36,508 --> 00:20:39,185
Are you going to sell mouthwash?

453
00:20:39,219 --> 00:20:40,324
Look at that.

454
00:20:40,346 --> 00:20:41,269
What are you talking about?

455
00:20:41,294 --> 00:20:42,802
He's really having a seizure!

456
00:20:43,180 --> 00:20:43,983
Uncle!

457
00:20:45,241 --> 00:20:46,368
Guys!

458
00:20:46,484 --> 00:20:48,382
Please spread out and give him some space.

459
00:20:48,407 --> 00:20:49,336
He needs to breathe.

460
00:20:49,358 --> 00:20:51,294
Please spread out. Spread out.

461
00:20:51,773 --> 00:20:53,297
Is this yours? Can I borrow it?

462
00:20:54,248 --> 00:20:55,402
Careful.

463
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:57,983
Hey, don't touch him.

464
00:20:58,274 --> 00:20:59,983
Let him have a seizure.

465
00:21:00,013 --> 00:21:01,103
Give me the spoon.

466
00:21:01,588 --> 00:21:03,801
Hey, we don't need the spoon.

467
00:21:03,930 --> 00:21:05,358
We don't want to hurt him.

468
00:21:05,385 --> 00:21:07,988
- Please spread out and let him breathe.
- Hey, what's going on?

469
00:21:08,149 --> 00:21:09,736
The uncle is having a seizure.
Come on, help him.

470
00:21:09,776 --> 00:21:10,702
Back up, please.

471
00:21:10,780 --> 00:21:12,601
Don't crowd around.
Let's keep the air circulating.

472
00:21:14,254 --> 00:21:15,395
Please back up, everyone.

473
00:21:16,032 --> 00:21:17,503
He's a rescuer. He can help.

474
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:19,977
Someone's having a seizure at the market.

475
00:21:20,148 --> 00:21:21,468
We're in the canteen.

476
00:21:21,706 --> 00:21:22,998
Please come ASAP.

477
00:21:23,441 --> 00:21:24,998
Okay, please hurry.

478
00:21:25,742 --> 00:21:26,601
Yeah.

479
00:21:27,983 --> 00:21:29,604
Has anyone called 1669?

480
00:21:29,662 --> 00:21:30,700
Yes, I have.

481
00:21:30,871 --> 00:21:31,702
Okay.

482
00:21:31,979 --> 00:21:34,365
Is anyone here his relative or a friend?

483
00:21:34,398 --> 00:21:35,201
Anyone?

484
00:21:36,322 --> 00:21:37,303
I don't see anyone.

485
00:21:37,758 --> 00:21:39,062
Did anyone witness it from the start?

486
00:21:39,085 --> 00:21:40,229
When did the seizure begin?

487
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:41,980
About two or three minutes ago.

488
00:21:44,974 --> 00:21:45,977
What can we do?

489
00:21:46,632 --> 00:21:48,186
Nothing. We don't have the equipment.

490
00:21:48,220 --> 00:21:49,502
We'll have to wait for the ambulance.

491
00:21:51,500 --> 00:21:52,597
Please move back.

492
00:21:53,173 --> 00:21:54,892
Let's keep the air circulating, guys.

493
00:22:05,168 --> 00:22:07,499
You messed around too much, you know?

494
00:22:07,522 --> 00:22:09,499
That man almost died for real.

495
00:22:09,644 --> 00:22:12,903
Hey, but we managed to save his life.

496
00:22:15,750 --> 00:22:17,472
I've had training before,

497
00:22:17,490 --> 00:22:19,982
but I've never experienced anything
like this in real life.

498
00:22:20,013 --> 00:22:20,705
Wow.

499
00:22:21,084 --> 00:22:22,198
That got my heart racing.

500
00:22:22,989 --> 00:22:24,488
But you do it every day.

501
00:22:24,514 --> 00:22:26,402
I guess it's just a normal day for you.

502
00:22:27,143 --> 00:22:28,400
It's not normal.

503
00:22:29,037 --> 00:22:31,598
Saving lives feels special every time.

504
00:22:32,291 --> 00:22:34,097
Saving them is like saving myself.

505
00:22:35,351 --> 00:22:37,330
It makes me feel useful to others.

506
00:22:40,517 --> 00:22:45,102
I hope going out in the field with you
will help me do better in the exam.

507
00:22:45,862 --> 00:22:46,800
Of course you will.

508
00:22:47,030 --> 00:22:51,610
From what I see, I'd say…
you're definitely going to pass.

509
00:22:51,840 --> 00:22:52,697
I guarantee it.

510
00:22:53,365 --> 00:22:54,493
That's great.

511
00:22:54,521 --> 00:22:57,980
I'll finally be able to apply for
an international airline.

512
00:22:58,110 --> 00:23:00,700
So Lion and I can fly at the same level.

513
00:23:00,934 --> 00:23:01,971
Woo!

514
00:23:04,734 --> 00:23:06,205
Your life goal is all about him, huh?

515
00:23:06,448 --> 00:23:11,296
Yeah, I need to try to improve myself
so I can match him.

516
00:23:13,890 --> 00:23:16,099
Why are you the only one trying
and not him too?

517
00:23:18,188 --> 00:23:21,202
Well, he's higher up than I am.

518
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:23,200
I need to climb up.

519
00:23:26,070 --> 00:23:27,204
That sounds so exhausting.

520
00:23:30,576 --> 00:23:31,598
It is exhausting.

521
00:23:31,629 --> 00:23:35,598
How good do I have to be
for it to be enough?

522
00:23:36,084 --> 00:23:37,976
Both for my dad and my boyfriend.

523
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:51,401
If you were my boyfriend,
you wouldn't have to try so hard.

524
00:23:52,278 --> 00:23:53,897
I'd love you for who you are.

525
00:24:11,417 --> 00:24:13,604
Sorry for getting emotional.

526
00:24:14,518 --> 00:24:16,598
I should go.

527
00:24:17,397 --> 00:24:19,976
Thanks for letting me experience
the real thing today.

528
00:24:21,948 --> 00:24:22,703
Bye.

529
00:24:51,500 --> 00:24:52,653
- Surprise!
- Hey!

530
00:24:52,765 --> 00:24:53,499
Hey!

531
00:24:54,266 --> 00:24:54,802
Oh!

532
00:24:55,096 --> 00:24:56,002
Lion!

533
00:24:56,614 --> 00:24:58,402
What are you doing here?

534
00:24:58,592 --> 00:25:00,297
I thought you were flying.

535
00:25:00,635 --> 00:25:03,983
Come on. I swapped flights with a friend
to spend time with you.

536
00:25:04,285 --> 00:25:05,299
I've missed you.

537
00:25:07,110 --> 00:25:09,702
If you've missed me,
you should've come to see me more often.

538
00:25:11,321 --> 00:25:14,401
My flight schedule has been really hectic.

539
00:25:14,705 --> 00:25:17,303
Look, my body
can barely even deal with it.

540
00:25:17,869 --> 00:25:20,696
I just wanted to come
and recharge with you.

541
00:25:21,560 --> 00:25:23,097
Can I hug you one more time?

542
00:25:34,380 --> 00:25:35,800
But actually,

543
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,200
I have something to tell you.

544
00:25:41,020 --> 00:25:42,100
What is it?

545
00:25:46,284 --> 00:25:47,200
Is it…

546
00:25:48,491 --> 00:25:49,899
Is it serious?

547
00:25:50,900 --> 00:25:54,202
Mm…I've been thinking about this
for a few days now.

548
00:25:55,460 --> 00:25:57,004
I haven't been able to eat or sleep.

549
00:25:58,682 --> 00:26:00,299
I feel so guilty.

550
00:26:03,330 --> 00:26:05,299
Just tell me. I can accept anything.

551
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:07,102
It's better than
hiding things from me.

552
00:26:08,257 --> 00:26:09,165
(One week.)

553
00:26:09,601 --> 00:26:11,002
I'm giving you one week.

554
00:26:11,260 --> 00:26:12,401
Break it off for good.

555
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:14,352
Then tell Kanit yourself.

556
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:20,200
Well, all this time,

557
00:26:20,943 --> 00:26:23,650
I may not have taken good care of you,

558
00:26:25,380 --> 00:26:26,499
but from now on,

559
00:26:28,829 --> 00:26:32,201
I'll do my best to be a good boyfriend.

560
00:26:36,619 --> 00:26:37,354
Kanit…

561
00:26:38,508 --> 00:26:39,200
Hmm?

562
00:26:44,750 --> 00:26:45,576
Hey.

563
00:26:46,352 --> 00:26:47,402
What are you doing?

564
00:26:48,665 --> 00:26:49,297
Hey.

565
00:26:54,977 --> 00:26:56,198
Are you serious?

566
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:15,299
I feel guilty about
missing our dinner that day.

567
00:27:16,310 --> 00:27:19,100
I know how much you've done for me.

568
00:27:20,340 --> 00:27:21,977
And I want you to know

569
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:26,502
how lucky I feel
to have you as my boyfriend.

570
00:27:30,884 --> 00:27:32,097
I hope you like it.

571
00:27:41,468 --> 00:27:43,502
I really hate homewreckers.

572
00:27:47,910 --> 00:27:49,202
How did you follow me here?

573
00:27:52,139 --> 00:27:54,370
I just came to warn you
out of good intentions.

574
00:27:55,560 --> 00:27:57,983
Keep your good intentions to yourself.

575
00:28:09,597 --> 00:28:10,303
Go away.

576
00:28:10,472 --> 00:28:11,980
Or I'll call security to get you out.

577
00:28:12,619 --> 00:28:13,980
Stop talking to Lion.

578
00:28:14,678 --> 00:28:16,404
Don't you know he already has a boyfriend?

579
00:28:16,631 --> 00:28:18,598
I do, but they're about to break up.

580
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:24,699
Then can't you wait
until they actually break up first?

581
00:28:24,724 --> 00:28:25,402
Hmm?

582
00:28:25,582 --> 00:28:27,097
Can't you wait?

583
00:28:27,591 --> 00:28:30,297
Or is shamelessness
a trait of homewreckers?

584
00:28:34,881 --> 00:28:36,500
Hey! Get out!

585
00:28:36,860 --> 00:28:38,200
Are you going to leave peacefully or not?

586
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:40,090
If not, I'll call security
and have you thrown out.

587
00:28:40,337 --> 00:28:41,201
Call them.

588
00:28:41,377 --> 00:28:42,204
Go ahead.

589
00:28:42,419 --> 00:28:45,401
I'm going to yell so loud that
there's a shameless person in this room.

590
00:28:45,522 --> 00:28:47,450
If you're that desperate,
I'll help you out.

591
00:28:47,800 --> 00:28:48,548
Fine.

592
00:28:50,908 --> 00:28:51,602
Hey!

593
00:28:51,930 --> 00:28:53,195
Give me back my phone!

594
00:28:54,462 --> 00:28:55,979
Go ahead and call them.

595
00:28:56,810 --> 00:28:58,602
If you want your phone back so badly,

596
00:28:59,202 --> 00:29:01,242
say you'll stop messing
with someone else's partner.

597
00:29:01,275 --> 00:29:02,699
Why should I listen to you?

598
00:29:04,035 --> 00:29:05,302
If you don't,

599
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:07,499
I'll…

600
00:29:18,955 --> 00:29:20,195
(Hello, Mr. Veha.)

601
00:29:20,734 --> 00:29:22,045
Someone has broken into my room.

602
00:29:22,078 --> 00:29:23,401
Come up and deal with him.

603
00:29:23,899 --> 00:29:24,597
Hey!

604
00:29:24,720 --> 00:29:25,697
Are you serious?

605
00:29:28,830 --> 00:29:29,705
Let go!
Let go of me!

606
00:29:30,488 --> 00:29:32,129
I won't stop until you
stop being a homewrecker!

607
00:29:32,161 --> 00:29:33,499
Let go of me! Let go!

608
00:29:33,522 --> 00:29:34,601
This isn't over!

609
00:29:34,755 --> 00:29:35,674
Let go!

610
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:38,690
WAR OF THE WANNABE ANGELS

611
00:29:38,998 --> 00:29:42,802
(The only thing you're good at
is stealing other people's men.)

612
00:29:42,922 --> 00:29:45,134
(Even if being shameless
is something I can't fix, )

613
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,801
(if he can't get enough
of my pretty face, )

614
00:29:47,887 --> 00:29:50,280
(I guess I have my doctor
to thank for that.)

615
00:29:50,317 --> 00:29:51,897
(Oh, really?)

616
00:29:52,085 --> 00:29:54,625
(Then maybe your doctor
can help treat the wounds)

617
00:29:54,656 --> 00:29:57,976
(after I slap the hell out of you!)

618
00:29:58,211 --> 00:29:59,100
Hey.

619
00:29:59,561 --> 00:30:01,334
You came to see me, so focus on me.

620
00:30:01,364 --> 00:30:02,604
Stop being on your phone.

621
00:30:03,761 --> 00:30:07,499
I'm just talking to my friend
about something.

622
00:30:07,771 --> 00:30:09,699
But it's okay. I'm done now.

623
00:30:11,177 --> 00:30:12,397
I'm all yours again.

624
00:30:16,014 --> 00:30:18,197
When will we finally go public?

625
00:30:19,297 --> 00:30:20,702
You won't let me post our photos.

626
00:30:20,982 --> 00:30:22,401
I haven't met your parents.

627
00:30:22,474 --> 00:30:23,977
Only some of our friends know about us.

628
00:30:25,004 --> 00:30:26,804
I want to go public too,

629
00:30:27,137 --> 00:30:30,296
but my job isn't really
open-minded about it yet.

630
00:30:30,514 --> 00:30:31,601
Not yet?

631
00:30:31,884 --> 00:30:33,974
Isn't it already normal
in the aviation industry?

632
00:30:34,173 --> 00:30:36,600
It's not every airline.

633
00:30:38,715 --> 00:30:41,700
Have you thought about getting married?

634
00:30:43,223 --> 00:30:43,980
Of course.

635
00:30:44,711 --> 00:30:46,303
I already have plans for the future,

636
00:30:46,760 --> 00:30:48,897
but I want to keep them a surprise.

637
00:30:59,840 --> 00:31:01,979
Hey, stop it.

638
00:31:02,484 --> 00:31:05,201
Every time you come to see me,
you want to sleep together?

639
00:31:06,720 --> 00:31:07,798
Can we?

640
00:31:07,850 --> 00:31:11,401
No, I have to wake up early tomorrow,
and I also have an exam.

641
00:31:12,037 --> 00:31:13,093
Not even a little?

642
00:31:13,130 --> 00:31:14,200
No.

643
00:31:14,552 --> 00:31:16,601
I want to recharge my love battery.

644
00:31:17,096 --> 00:31:18,802
You can recharge by hugging.

645
00:31:19,044 --> 00:31:20,197
It's so much better.

646
00:31:21,648 --> 00:31:22,300
Alright.

647
00:31:22,768 --> 00:31:23,979
I'll just hug you then.

648
00:31:25,426 --> 00:31:26,497
It feels just as warm.

649
00:31:33,247 --> 00:31:33,976
(Come on!)

650
00:31:34,906 --> 00:31:35,600
(Why?)

651
00:31:36,617 --> 00:31:37,980
(Are you trying to steal my man?)

652
00:31:38,034 --> 00:31:38,900
(Stop!)

653
00:31:39,734 --> 00:31:40,702
(I've made my decision!)

654
00:31:41,600 --> 00:31:44,565
(A new face is better than
an old one anyway!)

655
00:32:00,210 --> 00:32:02,137
- Come on!
- Cheers!

656
00:32:02,165 --> 00:32:03,342
Cheers, bro!

657
00:32:03,417 --> 00:32:04,302
Let's go.

658
00:32:06,905 --> 00:32:07,980
Hey, To.

659
00:32:08,776 --> 00:32:10,500
When are you going to talk to him?

660
00:32:10,780 --> 00:32:12,702
Are you going to wait
until the next election?

661
00:32:13,208 --> 00:32:16,299
That guy asked for a week,
so I'm waiting for him.

662
00:32:16,491 --> 00:32:19,802
Meanwhile, that boy knows
he has a boyfriend,

663
00:32:20,131 --> 00:32:21,630
but he's definitely not
going to break up with him.

664
00:32:21,657 --> 00:32:23,099
So shameless.

665
00:32:24,802 --> 00:32:27,401
I think you need to tell him soon.

666
00:32:27,730 --> 00:32:29,330
You can't let him keep being fooled.

667
00:32:30,232 --> 00:32:31,202
I know.

668
00:32:32,737 --> 00:32:34,604
Part of me feels sorry for him,

669
00:32:35,642 --> 00:32:37,302
but another part of me feels like…

670
00:32:38,127 --> 00:32:39,700
it's none of my business.

671
00:32:40,485 --> 00:32:42,103
It is your business now.

672
00:32:42,711 --> 00:32:44,100
You took his money.

673
00:32:44,508 --> 00:32:45,250
Yeah.

674
00:32:46,367 --> 00:32:48,096
You've got to have morals.

675
00:32:49,037 --> 00:32:51,099
You should stand on the side
of what's right.

676
00:32:52,773 --> 00:32:53,400
Hey.
Huh?

677
00:32:54,026 --> 00:32:55,099
Or what?

678
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:56,382
Are you cheating with him?

679
00:32:56,401 --> 00:32:57,574
Hey!

680
00:32:58,260 --> 00:32:59,600
- What's wrong?
- I'm not!

681
00:32:59,623 --> 00:33:00,607
Maybe he's cheating with him.

682
00:33:00,644 --> 00:33:02,496
Why are you so invested
all of a sudden? Sit down.

683
00:33:02,850 --> 00:33:03,622
Don't do that.

684
00:33:03,897 --> 00:33:04,884
Sit down.

685
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:06,974
Fine.

686
00:33:09,893 --> 00:33:12,102
Once he finishes his annual assessment,

687
00:33:13,054 --> 00:33:15,800
if that thick-browed dog-face
still doesn't confess,

688
00:33:16,594 --> 00:33:17,982
I'll do it myself.

689
00:33:18,271 --> 00:33:19,001
Good.

690
00:33:21,030 --> 00:33:22,997
Beer, continue.

691
00:33:24,108 --> 00:33:24,644
Go.

692
00:33:24,853 --> 00:33:29,983
♪ If your heart leans toward me,
give me a sign ♪

693
00:33:31,388 --> 00:33:36,299
♪ Do not leave me hanging,
waiting for that line ♪

694
00:33:38,210 --> 00:33:38,749
(This year, )

695
00:33:38,777 --> 00:33:40,751
(the assessment is going to
be much more challenging)

696
00:33:40,773 --> 00:33:43,198
(to raise our airline's standards.)

697
00:33:53,521 --> 00:33:55,037
(So today, )

698
00:33:55,065 --> 00:33:57,696
(unexpected situations may be added)

699
00:33:57,880 --> 00:34:00,105
(to test all our cabin crew's
quick thinking.)

700
00:34:00,231 --> 00:34:02,717
(Please stay calm and do your best.)

701
00:34:02,728 --> 00:34:03,703
(Good luck.)

702
00:34:04,155 --> 00:34:06,797
You'll enter the water and stay together.

703
00:34:06,888 --> 00:34:08,629
Then imagine the rescue team arrives.

704
00:34:08,660 --> 00:34:09,979
Switch to this hand-holding position.

705
00:34:10,330 --> 00:34:12,511
Maintain your body temperature.

706
00:34:12,536 --> 00:34:13,659
Rescuers are here.

707
00:34:13,690 --> 00:34:15,398
Call for help!

708
00:34:15,517 --> 00:34:17,077
Kick your legs a little.
They can't see you.

709
00:34:17,110 --> 00:34:18,302
They can't see you like that.

710
00:34:18,478 --> 00:34:19,736
Kick your feet,

711
00:34:19,970 --> 00:34:21,432
Okay.

712
00:34:25,551 --> 00:34:27,604
Hey, eat properly.

713
00:34:27,684 --> 00:34:29,001
Why are you rushing like that?

714
00:34:30,120 --> 00:34:32,697
Whoa. Slow down.

715
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,802
You're eating like you've been starving.

716
00:34:35,592 --> 00:34:37,500
I can't help it. It's your treat.

717
00:34:37,641 --> 00:34:38,802
I have to make the most of it.

718
00:34:40,364 --> 00:34:41,691
Hey, sit properly.

719
00:34:43,525 --> 00:34:45,974
I'm just sitting the traditional Thai way.

720
00:34:47,296 --> 00:34:50,699
This meal is to thank you for tutoring me.

721
00:34:50,790 --> 00:34:51,977
It's not about the debt.

722
00:34:52,585 --> 00:34:54,201
Wait, this is free?

723
00:34:55,241 --> 00:34:55,902
Mm.

724
00:34:57,110 --> 00:34:57,976
Merci.

725
00:34:58,190 --> 00:34:59,054
Merci.

726
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:01,395
What are you saying?

727
00:35:02,030 --> 00:35:04,370
Merci, of course.
You don't know what it means?

728
00:35:04,631 --> 00:35:06,296
It's “thank you” in French.

729
00:35:06,534 --> 00:35:08,696
Whoa. How can you be a flight attendant?

730
00:35:09,031 --> 00:35:09,802
I know it.

731
00:35:10,007 --> 00:35:11,985
I studied French in high school.

732
00:35:12,016 --> 00:35:13,000
Listen.

733
00:35:13,440 --> 00:35:15,090
Hello, how are you?

734
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:17,410
I'm fine. Thank you. And you?

735
00:35:18,345 --> 00:35:19,047
Whoa.

736
00:35:19,980 --> 00:35:23,128
That's such a “Hello, Teacher, I'm fine.
Sit down, please” kind of thing to say.

737
00:35:23,548 --> 00:35:24,154
Totally.

738
00:35:24,182 --> 00:35:25,982
So what? Can you even speak it?

739
00:35:26,980 --> 00:35:27,604
Yeah.

740
00:35:27,885 --> 00:35:29,690
You're good at everything, huh?
Say something.

741
00:35:30,080 --> 00:35:32,570
Do you know that you are beautiful,

742
00:35:32,600 --> 00:35:35,570
so irresistible

743
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:39,370
that I couldn't help
but fall in love with you?

744
00:35:41,712 --> 00:35:42,496
You're stunned.
You're stunned, aren't you?

745
00:35:43,530 --> 00:35:46,219
My accent sounds like
I was born under the Eiffel Tower.

746
00:35:47,600 --> 00:35:49,979
More like you sleep
under the Eiffel Tower.

747
00:35:50,040 --> 00:35:51,798
- Hey.
- What language was that? Parseltongue?

748
00:35:54,155 --> 00:35:57,198
Hey, that's basically what I remember.

749
00:35:57,830 --> 00:35:58,902
It means something good.

750
00:35:59,380 --> 00:36:00,899
Something good? What does it mean?

751
00:36:06,210 --> 00:36:07,602
Hey, what are you doing?

752
00:36:17,194 --> 00:36:18,404
You're so beautiful.

753
00:36:19,560 --> 00:36:21,601
So beautiful
I almost couldn't stop myself.

754
00:36:23,192 --> 00:36:24,499
Can I hit on you?

755
00:36:34,714 --> 00:36:35,437
Say yes!
Say yes!

756
00:36:36,370 --> 00:36:37,099
Say yes!

757
00:36:37,127 --> 00:36:38,509
Oh, no.

758
00:36:38,537 --> 00:36:39,986
He's not proposing!

759
00:36:40,527 --> 00:36:41,597
No.

760
00:36:42,720 --> 00:36:44,899
Hey, what are you doing? Get up!

761
00:36:44,924 --> 00:36:46,097
Go back to your seat.

762
00:36:46,340 --> 00:36:48,057
- What's wrong with you?
- You're shy, aren't you?

763
00:36:48,103 --> 00:36:49,480
Shy, my ass!

764
00:36:49,647 --> 00:36:50,600
I can tell.

765
00:36:55,127 --> 00:36:56,499
Alright, stop being shy.

766
00:36:56,527 --> 00:36:57,697
Shy, my ass!

767
00:36:58,263 --> 00:36:59,200
You're embarrassing.

768
00:36:59,401 --> 00:37:00,770
You act like you don't like it,
but I can tell…

769
00:37:01,346 --> 00:37:02,705
you're waiting to be proposed to.

770
00:37:03,537 --> 00:37:04,400
Of course.

771
00:37:04,481 --> 00:37:05,576
But not by you.

772
00:37:05,617 --> 00:37:06,404
I know.

773
00:37:09,176 --> 00:37:11,197
So, how are things with you
and your boyfriend?

774
00:37:12,090 --> 00:37:13,200
Any updates?

775
00:37:13,471 --> 00:37:15,102
Why do you ask? There's nothing.

776
00:37:16,934 --> 00:37:17,903
I mean,

777
00:37:18,567 --> 00:37:20,401
did he do anything suspicious again?

778
00:37:21,718 --> 00:37:23,401
Hmm, no.

779
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:25,976
He even got sweeter. Look.

780
00:37:26,394 --> 00:37:27,976
He got me a new bracelet.

781
00:37:29,035 --> 00:37:33,703
And he said he'd make more time for me.

782
00:37:34,537 --> 00:37:36,899
It's so romantic.

783
00:37:51,309 --> 00:37:52,897
That's so disgusting.

784
00:37:53,219 --> 00:37:55,500
Try learning some social manners.

785
00:37:55,662 --> 00:37:57,300
Don't only stick to survival skills.

786
00:37:58,001 --> 00:37:58,899
I'm full.

787
00:37:59,244 --> 00:38:01,004
Thank you so much.

788
00:38:01,583 --> 00:38:03,974
If I had to pay for it myself,
I'd never come to a place like this.

789
00:38:04,035 --> 00:38:05,002
It's so expensive.

790
00:38:05,374 --> 00:38:07,893
Look, I'll treat you
to an even bigger meal

791
00:38:07,920 --> 00:38:10,906
if I get promoted
to cabin crew supervisor

792
00:38:10,936 --> 00:38:14,398
and use my portfolio
to apply for Lion's airline.

793
00:38:14,684 --> 00:38:20,499
Then I'll get to fly with him
and we'll get to spend more time together.

794
00:38:20,677 --> 00:38:23,797
The proposal scene in my dream
would finally come true.

795
00:38:26,940 --> 00:38:27,650
Hey.

796
00:38:30,871 --> 00:38:32,435
I'm sorry to ruin your dream...

797
00:38:32,460 --> 00:38:33,004
Hey.

798
00:38:33,173 --> 00:38:35,072
You're calling me delusional again,
aren't you?

799
00:38:35,103 --> 00:38:36,607
Some people really propose...

800
00:38:36,640 --> 00:38:37,982
Your boyfriend is cheating on you.

801
00:38:41,810 --> 00:38:43,090
What are you talking about?

802
00:38:50,117 --> 00:38:50,802
Hey.

803
00:38:51,533 --> 00:38:52,398
Let's talk inside.

804
00:38:52,607 --> 00:38:53,430
Let's go. We're all soaked.

805
00:38:53,451 --> 00:38:55,102
No. We'll talk here.

806
00:38:55,217 --> 00:38:56,502
Tell me everything.

807
00:39:05,272 --> 00:39:07,530
Your boyfriend is seeing a flight
attendant from another airline.

808
00:39:10,016 --> 00:39:11,220
That jerk asked if he could tell you himself.

809
00:39:11,248 --> 00:39:13,097
I thought he would've told you by now.

810
00:39:14,251 --> 00:39:15,604
How long have you known?

811
00:39:17,460 --> 00:39:18,272
Over a week now.

812
00:39:19,840 --> 00:39:21,100
Then why didn't you tell me?

813
00:39:21,868 --> 00:39:23,703
Well, he asked to talk to you himself.

814
00:39:24,031 --> 00:39:26,397
I didn't think
he'd keep stalling like this.

815
00:39:27,225 --> 00:39:28,922
Did you have to agree
to what he asked?

816
00:39:28,950 --> 00:39:30,850
Or what? He hired you, didn't he?

817
00:39:31,678 --> 00:39:33,460
Oh, you're so easy to buy.

818
00:39:33,488 --> 00:39:35,398
Anyone with money can be your boss.

819
00:39:35,665 --> 00:39:36,173
I just...

820
00:39:36,197 --> 00:39:37,497
Save your excuses.

821
00:39:37,970 --> 00:39:39,802
Your words can't be trusted anymore.

822
00:39:40,072 --> 00:39:41,982
Trust doesn't just
come floating in with the water.

823
00:39:42,010 --> 00:39:43,800
You're no different from scammers.

824
00:39:45,068 --> 00:39:46,595
I've told you now.

825
00:39:47,426 --> 00:39:48,834
So go and break up with him.

826
00:39:48,857 --> 00:39:50,697
You don't get to tell me what to do.

827
00:39:50,980 --> 00:39:51,983
From now on,

828
00:39:52,080 --> 00:39:53,506
I won't make you work for me anymore.

829
00:39:53,533 --> 00:39:55,600
- Hey!
- And the rest of the money you owe me?

830
00:39:55,813 --> 00:39:57,410
I'll consider
it a donation to a stray dog.

831
00:39:58,299 --> 00:39:59,000
Hey!

832
00:39:59,201 --> 00:40:00,404
Hear me out!

833
00:40:01,979 --> 00:40:03,401
Give me a chance!

834
00:40:03,979 --> 00:40:04,699
Hey!

835
00:40:05,518 --> 00:40:06,299
Kanit!

836
00:40:07,180 --> 00:40:08,097
I'm sorry!

837
00:40:17,791 --> 00:40:18,804
Damn it!

838
00:40:27,457 --> 00:40:29,011
Everyone, get into position.

839
00:40:29,546 --> 00:40:31,497
Ready? Lift your hips up.

840
00:40:32,194 --> 00:40:34,900
Engage your core. Now lower into a plank.

841
00:40:35,226 --> 00:40:36,776
Kick your right leg three times.

842
00:40:36,807 --> 00:40:38,700
Exhale. One.

843
00:40:40,352 --> 00:40:41,348
Two.

844
00:40:42,537 --> 00:40:43,300
Three.

845
00:40:43,385 --> 00:40:44,499
Very good.

846
00:40:44,884 --> 00:40:47,601
Now sit cross-legged.

847
00:40:48,714 --> 00:40:51,800
I just need everyone to concentrate
and focus on the right thing.

848
00:40:52,617 --> 00:40:54,402
Take a deep breath.

849
00:40:55,721 --> 00:40:56,703
Breathe out.

850
00:41:00,158 --> 00:41:00,800
Hey.

851
00:41:01,770 --> 00:41:02,497
Kanit.

852
00:41:02,998 --> 00:41:03,973
Hey.

853
00:41:04,365 --> 00:41:05,398
How did you get in here?

854
00:41:05,579 --> 00:41:06,997
This place is members-only.

855
00:41:07,413 --> 00:41:08,842
I want to apologize.

856
00:41:09,150 --> 00:41:11,496
You didn't pick up or reply to me at all.

857
00:41:11,830 --> 00:41:13,197
Silence is my reply.

858
00:41:18,082 --> 00:41:18,800
Hey.

859
00:41:19,611 --> 00:41:21,644
Can you focus on me for 5 minutes?

860
00:41:23,568 --> 00:41:26,201
Even one second is too much
for someone like you.

861
00:41:27,813 --> 00:41:29,201
What do you want me to do?

862
00:41:29,491 --> 00:41:30,802
I really feel guilty.

863
00:41:31,765 --> 00:41:32,994
Do you want me to
become a monk for you?

864
00:41:33,010 --> 00:41:34,400
How long do you want
me to stay ordained?

865
00:41:36,272 --> 00:41:38,120
Even if you stayed ordained
until you reached nirvana,

866
00:41:38,150 --> 00:41:39,610
I still wouldn't forgive you.

867
00:41:39,632 --> 00:41:41,930
Does yoga not teach you to forgive at all?

868
00:41:42,266 --> 00:41:43,819
It's yoga, not Dharma.

869
00:41:44,030 --> 00:41:44,896
Besides,

870
00:41:45,137 --> 00:41:48,650
my motto is that if you keep forgiving,
you'll never get your revenge.

871
00:41:50,567 --> 00:41:51,303
Hey.

872
00:41:51,813 --> 00:41:53,102
Hear me out.

873
00:41:54,001 --> 00:41:54,826
Excuse me.

874
00:41:55,888 --> 00:41:57,468
This guy is not a member.

875
00:41:57,505 --> 00:42:00,053
I don't know how he got in here.
He's really bothering me right now.

876
00:42:00,072 --> 00:42:01,296
I'm losing my focus.

877
00:42:01,540 --> 00:42:02,299
Excuse me.
Kanit!

878
00:42:02,973 --> 00:42:03,968
Please go outside.

879
00:42:04,317 --> 00:42:04,906
Hey!

880
00:42:04,937 --> 00:42:06,800
Hey! Hear me out!

881
00:42:07,082 --> 00:42:07,651
Hey!
Hey!

882
00:42:09,761 --> 00:42:11,922
Abhayadānaṃ āmisadānaṃ jināti.

883
00:42:11,954 --> 00:42:13,730
Forgiveness is the highest form of giving.

884
00:42:13,894 --> 00:42:14,902
Do you hear me?

885
00:42:14,954 --> 00:42:15,675
Please come with us.

886
00:42:15,728 --> 00:42:16,834
Hear me out!

887
00:42:17,725 --> 00:42:18,404
Hey!

888
00:42:25,320 --> 00:42:28,149
SUVARNABHUMI AIRPORT

889
00:42:28,188 --> 00:42:31,297
Hey, have you watched that series
Me and Thee?

890
00:42:31,475 --> 00:42:33,500
Mr. Thee and Nong Lookpeach, you know.

891
00:42:35,139 --> 00:42:35,971
Yes, I have.

892
00:42:36,722 --> 00:42:39,302
There's no one rich and sincere like that.

893
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:41,976
Trust me. Mr. Thee exists.
You'll find yours.

894
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:45,570
I'M SORRY.

895
00:42:48,402 --> 00:42:49,204
Hey.

896
00:42:50,050 --> 00:42:50,800
Look.

897
00:42:51,340 --> 00:42:55,100
Is he helping you catch the cheater,
or is he actually trying to win you over?

898
00:42:55,349 --> 00:42:56,416
This is straight out of a romantic movie.

899
00:42:56,450 --> 00:42:57,201
Look!

900
00:42:57,631 --> 00:42:59,400
Win me over? He's embarrassing.

901
00:43:01,477 --> 00:43:02,202
Let's go.

902
00:43:07,210 --> 00:43:08,502
Dear passengers,

903
00:43:11,468 --> 00:43:13,201
My name is Panupong Sookklaharn.

904
00:43:13,386 --> 00:43:14,352
My nickname is Toto.

905
00:43:14,382 --> 00:43:15,496
I'm a rescuer.

906
00:43:16,091 --> 00:43:18,402
I wronged Mr. Kanit Sakdatawee.

907
00:43:19,045 --> 00:43:19,974
His nickname is Nong Nit.

908
00:43:20,957 --> 00:43:22,601
He's a flight attendant.

909
00:43:23,380 --> 00:43:25,497
What I did was terrible and unforgivable,

910
00:43:26,280 --> 00:43:27,530
but you should forgive me anyway.

911
00:43:30,470 --> 00:43:31,402
Please, Nong Nit.

912
00:43:31,478 --> 00:43:33,798
Consider forgiving Toto.

913
00:43:41,300 --> 00:43:42,299
I've gone this far.

914
00:43:42,816 --> 00:43:44,299
You have to forgive me.

915
00:44:02,736 --> 00:44:03,497
Hey!

916
00:44:04,448 --> 00:44:06,801
Whoa, that's harsh.

917
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:09,971
That's harsh, isn't it?

918
00:44:11,549 --> 00:44:12,598
Really harsh.

919
00:44:19,715 --> 00:44:20,405
Fine.

920
00:44:21,580 --> 00:44:22,998
You're playing hard to get, huh?

921
00:44:23,050 --> 00:44:24,103
You're gonna get it.

922
00:44:31,290 --> 00:44:32,500
(Next Episode)
Someone like Lion

923
00:44:32,616 --> 00:44:34,991
is more worried about losing his image
than losing love.

924
00:44:35,084 --> 00:44:36,770
To deal with him,

925
00:44:36,890 --> 00:44:39,497
you need a team and a production.

926
00:44:39,640 --> 00:44:40,262
SIDE PIECE'S CAR

927
00:44:40,281 --> 00:44:41,450
I'm calling the cops on you!

928
00:44:41,469 --> 00:44:42,602
I'll make sure you lose everything!

929
00:44:42,628 --> 00:44:44,571
I just want you to know
that being a side piece is wrong.

930
00:44:44,610 --> 00:44:45,660
Give me your hand.

931
00:44:45,973 --> 00:44:46,788
Thank you.

932
00:44:46,831 --> 00:44:47,804
Same old trick.

933
00:44:47,831 --> 00:44:50,802
Time to reclaim your dignity, Nopnapha.

934
00:44:51,191 --> 00:44:52,170
You missed me.

935
00:44:52,380 --> 00:44:53,402
So here I am.

936
00:44:53,702 --> 00:44:55,608
If Lion can't make your dream come true,

937
00:44:55,640 --> 00:44:57,250
why don't you find someone else who can?
